WEBVTT

00:02.690 --> 00:05.523
<i>Now the story of a wealthy family</i>
<i>who lost everything...</i>

00:05.626 --> 00:07.560
<i>and the one son</i>
<i>who had no choice...</i>

00:07.662 --> 00:09.926
<i>but to keep them all together.</i>

00:15.236 --> 00:17.363
<i>It's</i> Arrested Development.

00:20.741 --> 00:23.301
<i>Low-carb diets</i>
<i>are sweeping the nation...</i>

00:23.411 --> 00:25.436
but some local businesses
are being left in the dust.

00:25.546 --> 00:27.980
- And the latest on Iraq...
- Hey, George Michael.

00:28.082 --> 00:31.142
They're gonna show that interview you did.
We're gonna watch it on Thursday, okay?

00:31.252 --> 00:33.550
- I'll make some popcorn.
- <i>Popcorn? Really? Cool.</i>

00:33.654 --> 00:36.248
- Yeah, the hell with Atkins, huh?
- Oh. Yeah.

00:36.357 --> 00:38.723
Oh, why blow it now?
I'll fry up some bacon.

00:38.826 --> 00:41.454
Uh, Dad...

00:43.064 --> 00:45.532
Buddy, you gotta
take it easy, okay?

00:45.633 --> 00:47.533
I'm showing this
as a model again.

00:47.635 --> 00:50.468
I don't want people to think
we've got shoddy workmanship.

00:52.740 --> 00:55.004
That might not
have been your fault.

00:55.109 --> 00:57.600
I know. Nothing works
in this house.

00:57.712 --> 00:59.907
- Tell me about it.
- Is that a shot at me?

01:00.014 --> 01:02.642
- <i>Probably.</i>
- Because for your information, I got a job.

01:02.750 --> 01:05.810
- Really? What kind of job?
- Beads.

01:05.920 --> 01:09.083
- Bees?
- Beads.
- Beads?

01:09.190 --> 01:12.387
- Gob's not on board.
- Beads are very big right now.

01:12.493 --> 01:15.189
Uh, anklets,
necklaces, you name it.

01:15.296 --> 01:18.094
- Bracelets?
- But I'll need some start-up money.

01:18.199 --> 01:20.531
I'm in. But we're
gonna need a lot.

01:20.635 --> 01:22.762
Beads aren't cheap.
Are beads cheap?

01:22.870 --> 01:24.963
Gob, shouldn't you
be in bed?

01:25.072 --> 01:27.097
Well, we got a meeting
with Dad's attorney today.

01:27.208 --> 01:29.108
He's gonna want me to
take a lie-detector test...

01:29.210 --> 01:31.940
to use as evidence
in Dad's trial, but, uh, I don't want to.

01:32.046 --> 01:34.514
What if they ask about a magic trick?
I just... I can't risk it.

01:34.615 --> 01:38.517
They're not gonna ask you anything.
They want me to take the polygraph test.

01:38.619 --> 01:40.780
But... I'm the oldest.

01:40.888 --> 01:43.379
- The matriarch, if you will.
- Sure. I will.

01:43.491 --> 01:47.450
Listen, I have to do this to help out Dad,
and you don't know anything about our business.

01:47.561 --> 01:51.657
<i>Gob, I'm not looking for a partner. And,</i>
<i>believe me, if I was, it would not be you.</i>

01:51.766 --> 01:54.064
Oh. Good.

01:54.168 --> 01:57.296
Well, I'll start my own business.
How hard can it be?

01:57.405 --> 01:59.498
Z-z-z-z-z!

01:59.607 --> 02:01.336
Bz-z-z-z-z-z!

02:01.442 --> 02:03.808
We'll see who
brings in more honey.

02:03.911 --> 02:06.243
{ Buzzing]

02:06.347 --> 02:08.713
- He's thinking about bees again.
- Oh.

02:08.816 --> 02:12.047
I'm not just gonna cut you a check so you can
throw it away on another failed business.

02:12.153 --> 02:14.519
Hey, "Mommy, What Will I
Look Like?" should have worked.

02:14.622 --> 02:17.682
<i>[Man Narrating] Lindsay had once started</i>
<i>a photo-enhancing service...</i>

02:17.792 --> 02:20.886
<i>which gave new parents a glimpse at</i>
<i>what their infants would look like...</i>

02:20.995 --> 02:23.020
<i>in half a century.</i>

02:23.130 --> 02:26.827
<i>Hey, you put an ugly kid in, you can't be</i>
<i>surprised when an ugly adult comes out.</i>

02:26.934 --> 02:30.529
Look, I need to become self-reliant.
It's not gonna last with Tobias.

02:30.638 --> 02:34.506
He's completely oblivious.
He's got no idea how I'm feeling or thinking.

02:34.608 --> 02:38.510
- So there's no sex?
- I mean, how do you not have sex with me?

02:38.612 --> 02:41.274
It is a struggle.
I'll tell you what.

02:41.382 --> 02:43.282
I'll help you out,
but you gotta work.

02:43.384 --> 02:45.852
Great. Before you know it,
I'll be in the red.

02:45.953 --> 02:48.421
And you can take that
to the bank.

02:48.522 --> 02:50.513
I'm sure they'll
contact me first.

02:50.624 --> 02:53.354
<i>[Narrator] And that's when Michael</i>
<i>got a call that made him wish...</i>

02:53.461 --> 02:55.691
<i>he hadn't promised</i>
<i>his sister the money.</i>

02:55.796 --> 02:57.696
Hello.

02:57.798 --> 03:00.232
Kitty?

03:00.334 --> 03:03.895
<i>And later, the family waited for Michael</i>
<i>at the prison meeting room.</i>

03:04.004 --> 03:07.064
- How do you make money from it?
- I don't know. Honey?

03:07.174 --> 03:09.438
- Or just as gifts.
- Who'd want a bee as a gift?

03:09.543 --> 03:12.034
<i>While Buster and Annyong</i>
<i>waitedjust outside.</i>

03:12.146 --> 03:14.546
- Come on. Just let me have one bite.
- No.

03:14.648 --> 03:16.639
Mother said no carbohydrate for you
if you ever gonna...

03:16.751 --> 03:18.651
get girlfriend
that's not old lady.

03:18.753 --> 03:21.347
- At least I can get a girlfriend.
- I can get a girlfriend before you.

03:21.455 --> 03:24.083
- Oh, we'll see about that.
- Why aren't you in there?

03:24.191 --> 03:26.887
Oh, I was just keeping
Annyong company.

03:26.994 --> 03:30.088
Give me that bagel, you little... { Beeps]
Give it to me! { Beeps]

03:30.197 --> 03:33.257
Whoa! Our star witness!
Come here.

03:33.367 --> 03:35.733
Good to see you. You know what?
Don't get too close to me.

03:35.836 --> 03:38.737
'Cause I've got an itch you can't believe.
I think something laid eggs on me.

03:38.839 --> 03:42.570
- Thanks for the heads-up.
- That's okay. We've got your polygraph
set for tomorrow.

03:42.676 --> 03:44.940
- About that...
- <i>I'll tell them, Michael.</i>

03:46.480 --> 03:49.847
I won't do it.
I'm afraid of what I might know.

03:49.950 --> 03:51.941
You? No one wants you.
Does anyone want him?

03:52.052 --> 03:54.418
- Who would want him?
- They don't want you.

03:54.522 --> 03:57.320
- Good.
- I might not be the best witness either.

03:57.424 --> 04:00.086
- I got a phone call from Kitty this morning.
- His secretary?

04:00.194 --> 04:02.594
- My secretary.
- <i>She says that she's got some evidence...</i>

04:02.696 --> 04:05.426
and she's threatening to bring down
the company unless we meet her demands.

04:05.533 --> 04:07.433
<i>[Gob]</i>
<i>Oh, that is just great.</i>

04:07.535 --> 04:11.767
And now I'm expected to climb back
on top of Kitty and do my thing again.

04:11.872 --> 04:13.806
I mean, this family
runs into problems, it's...

04:13.908 --> 04:15.808
"Oh, let's have Gob
{ Beeps] our way out of it."

04:15.910 --> 04:19.141
- What is the matter with you?
- It's me that she wants to meet with, Gob.

04:19.245 --> 04:21.646
Oh. Good.

04:21.749 --> 04:24.047
Now, what does she have, Dad?
I need to know.

04:24.151 --> 04:26.278
No, you can't know.
We got to keep you nice and clean, Michael.

04:26.387 --> 04:30.323
- Especially if you're going
to take that lie detector test.
- He is absolutely right.

04:30.424 --> 04:32.756
<i>[George] Find out what Kitty wants</i>
<i>andjust give it to her...</i>

04:32.860 --> 04:35.055
<i>but don't find out</i>
<i>what she knows.</i>

04:35.162 --> 04:38.393
Michael, you can
save this business.

04:38.499 --> 04:40.899
You are the only one
who can do it.

04:41.001 --> 04:44.562
<i>Yeah, besides me, right? But I kind of</i>
<i>got my hands full with these babies.</i>

04:44.672 --> 04:46.230
- <i>He's got bees.!</i>
- <i>No bees.!</i>

04:46.340 --> 04:48.274
- <i>Get it.!</i>
- <i>[Jar Rolling]</i>

04:48.375 --> 04:50.707
They don't allow you
to have bees in here.

04:50.811 --> 04:53.302
<i>[Narrator] And business was slow</i>
<i>at the banana stand...</i>

04:53.414 --> 04:55.473
- <i>when George Michael made a new friend.</i>
- Hi.

04:56.817 --> 04:59.718
- Hi.
- Are bananas high in carbohydrates?

04:59.820 --> 05:01.720
<i>Oh, you're</i>
<i>on Atkins too?</i>

05:01.822 --> 05:05.223
Uh, yeah. Actually, that's, um...
that's why I'm gonna be on... on TV.

05:05.326 --> 05:08.887
- You are?
- I was interviewed for <i>Hindsight,</i> with John Beard.

05:08.996 --> 05:12.261
I, uh, I gave them a joke,
but I don't know if they're gonna use it.

05:12.366 --> 05:15.233
You know, thanks to this diet craze,
the last time we had a customer...

05:15.336 --> 05:17.065
the banana stand
was still green.

05:17.171 --> 05:21.505
Lose it. No, lose the whole kid.
We'll just go with the Iraq piece.

05:21.609 --> 05:24.442
- That's so cool.
- I guess.

05:24.545 --> 05:26.945
<i>[Girl]</i>
<i>You wanna watch over at my house?</i>

05:27.047 --> 05:29.709
Yeah, l-I guess.

05:31.051 --> 05:33.849
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>And Michael headed off to meet Kitty.</i>

05:33.954 --> 05:35.854
<i>Their last meeting</i>
<i>had ended poorly.</i>

05:35.956 --> 05:38.390
Say good-bye
to your company, Michael.

05:38.492 --> 05:40.687
- And say good-bye to these.
- No, no, no, no.

05:40.794 --> 05:44.059
<i>So Michael was understandably</i>
<i>anxious about their reunion.</i>

05:44.164 --> 05:46.359
Guess I do get to see them again, huh?
{ Chuckles]

05:46.467 --> 05:50.369
Can we please have one conversation
that's not about my rack, Michael?

05:50.471 --> 05:52.769
- Yeah.
- Maybe a better question would be...

05:52.873 --> 05:54.704
what evidence do I have
against you, because...

05:54.808 --> 05:56.708
No, no, no. I don't...
I don't wanna know.

05:56.810 --> 05:59.108
I just want to know
what you want.

05:59.213 --> 06:01.704
I'd like to be in charge
of the Bluth Company.

06:01.815 --> 06:05.046
Well, I want a hamburger and French fries,
but I can't have the bun or potatoes. Get real.

06:05.152 --> 06:08.644
I deserve it. Your father promised it
to me on the day he went to prison.

06:10.324 --> 06:12.884
Sounds like something
that he would do.

06:12.993 --> 06:16.793
<i>And if I can't be in charge, then I'm</i>
<i>going to have to tell the entire world...</i>

06:16.897 --> 06:19.627
that your father was
building houses overseas...

06:19.733 --> 06:22.133
- without paying...
- Whoa, whoa, whoa! Stop, stop. Stop.

06:22.236 --> 06:26.070
Act... No. Finish. Finish.
Um, without paying what? Taxes?

06:26.173 --> 06:29.734
Model houses, Michael.
Overseas.

06:29.843 --> 06:32.937
And he hid it...
{ Whispering] from the U.S. government.

06:33.047 --> 06:35.572
That's it? That's what
my dad's been hiding... back taxes?

06:35.683 --> 06:38.481
And unless you plan
on paying them...

06:38.585 --> 06:41.986
your dad's gonna be
in prison for a long time.

06:42.089 --> 06:45.923
No, we'll pay them. Forget it. We'll just...
We'll mortgage the company if we have to.

06:46.026 --> 06:48.586
We found money for those.
We'll find money for taxes. Good to see ya.

06:48.696 --> 06:53.759
Yeah. If I was in charge,
that would have been my first move too.

06:53.867 --> 06:56.392
<i>[Narrator] As Michael returned home,</i>
<i>George Michael was heading out...</i>

06:56.503 --> 06:58.994
<i>to meet the girl</i>
<i>from the banana stand.</i>

06:59.106 --> 07:01.506
Great news. The business
is gonna be okay.

07:01.608 --> 07:03.599
Yeah, I thought bananas
would be okay on the diet.

07:03.711 --> 07:06.111
No, l-I meant... Well...
You haven't been eating those, have you?

07:06.213 --> 07:09.705
- No. No. Not at all. Just some nuts.
- Good. Those are fine.

07:09.817 --> 07:12.650
What I meant was, I think we're gonna
be seeing Pop-Pop sooner than we thought.

07:12.753 --> 07:15.813
Huh?
Does that sound good?

07:15.923 --> 07:19.290
- Do you hear that rattle?
- It is very worrisome.

07:19.393 --> 07:22.089
- Hey, what the hell are you doing?
- Great news, Michael.

07:22.196 --> 07:24.824
We're thinking of purchasing
a Bluth model home.

07:24.932 --> 07:27.628
- <i>And let's check the oven.</i>
- { Clattering]

07:27.735 --> 07:29.635
Whoa! That doesn't
inspire confidence.

07:29.737 --> 07:32.672
Lindsay, the bead business
taking off, is it?

07:32.773 --> 07:35.708
Actually, I am the breadwinner, Michael,
as it turns out.

07:35.809 --> 07:37.834
I was walking
in a strange place today...

07:37.945 --> 07:40.209
<i>a place I'd never</i>
<i>set foot in before.</i>

07:40.314 --> 07:43.078
<i>[Narrator] Tobias, walking down a street</i>
<i>he'd been down many times...</i>

07:43.183 --> 07:47.415
<i>saw a book he'd written</i>
<i>years earlier as a psychiatrist.</i>

07:47.521 --> 07:49.887
<i>The book, initially unsuccessful,</i>
<i>had suddenly caught fire...</i>

07:49.990 --> 07:54.222
<i>although, strangely,</i>
<i>only in the gay community.</i>

07:54.328 --> 07:57.855
The book is huge. And I have a bit
of money coming my way as a result.

07:57.965 --> 08:01.196
<i>So if you'll excuse me, I'm going to</i>
<i>go upstairs and run the shower.</i>

08:01.301 --> 08:03.496
<i>Let me know</i>
<i>if it's too loud in the kitchen.</i>

08:03.604 --> 08:05.538
Okay, honey.

08:05.639 --> 08:08.836
So, your husband comes into some money,
and suddenly he's not so oblivious anymore, huh?

08:08.942 --> 08:11.240
Hey, now, this is not me
being shallow, Michael.

08:11.345 --> 08:13.870
He's written a self-help book
that's helping people.

08:13.981 --> 08:15.881
- That does take some insight.
- Listen.

08:15.983 --> 08:17.883
This better not mean
you're blowing off the bead store.

08:17.985 --> 08:21.751
Well, uh, seeing as though you brought it up,
maybe we should get out of this investment.

08:21.855 --> 08:24.517
- I mean, seriously, Michael... beads?
- I knew you'd do this.

08:24.625 --> 08:27.253
You work for three seconds,
and you find something easier and grab it.

08:27.361 --> 08:29.261
It's "Dip-A-Pet"
all over again.

08:29.363 --> 08:32.389
<i>[Narrator] Lindsay also had a brief foray</i>
<i>into what she had then hoped</i>...

08:32.499 --> 08:36.559
- Come back here!
- <i>would be the burgeoning fad</i>
<i>of custom pet coloring.</i>

08:36.669 --> 08:39.764
Well, that would've worked
if you'd sprung for a bigger sink.

08:39.873 --> 08:42.364
George Michael,
our show's about to start.

08:42.476 --> 08:45.036
- He went out on his date.
- A date?

08:45.145 --> 08:48.137
<i>But we had plans to</i>...
<i>A date with who?</i>

08:48.248 --> 08:51.877
Some girl. I mean, she barely has a face.
You couldn't pick her out of a lineup of one.

08:51.985 --> 08:54.317
<i>[Man On TV]</i>
<i>But first, the palaces of Iraq.</i>

08:54.421 --> 08:57.584
Trisha, tell us about these new
mini-palaces of Saddam's you've discovered.

08:57.691 --> 09:00.717
Our troops have been living here
for the last few days...

09:00.828 --> 09:04.628
and, as you can tell,
they've made themselves right at home.

09:04.731 --> 09:08.565
Now, a lot of this damage
is just due to shoddy workmanship...

09:08.669 --> 09:11.467
but the real surprise here
is that these homes...

09:11.572 --> 09:14.905
appear to be American-built
to begin with.

09:15.008 --> 09:16.942
There have been sanctions
against doing business...

09:17.044 --> 09:19.171
with Hussein's regime
since the early '90s...

09:19.279 --> 09:22.442
- <i>so who built them?</i>
- Does that look a little like our kitchen island?

09:22.549 --> 09:25.916
Well, whoever it is,
they're in a world of trouble.

09:26.019 --> 09:28.146
<i>[Narrator] Michael realized</i>
<i>that his father's crimes...</i>

09:28.255 --> 09:30.120
<i>might be bigger</i>
<i>than he thought.</i>

09:30.224 --> 09:35.025
There's a good chance
I may have committed some light treason.

09:35.129 --> 09:39.122
This might even be
considered light treason.

09:39.233 --> 09:41.827
Oh, my God.

09:48.942 --> 09:49.476
<i>[Narrator] Michael hadjust found out</i>
<i>his father might have committed...</i>

09:49.476 --> 09:53.412
<i>[Narrator] Michael hadjust found out</i>
<i>his father might have committed...</i>

09:53.514 --> 09:56.506
<i>some light treason</i>
<i>by building model homes in Iraq.</i>

09:56.617 --> 09:59.745
<i>And he tried to get ahold of Kitty,</i>
<i>who he knew had the evidence.</i>

09:59.853 --> 10:02.515
<i>Unfortunately,</i>
<i>Kitty was meeting with Gob at the time.</i>

10:02.623 --> 10:06.354
- What about hash browns?
- No, because hash browns are potatoes.

10:06.460 --> 10:08.860
So you really can't
eat anything on this diet.

10:08.962 --> 10:12.056
Wow. Wonder how this
is gonna affect my honey business?

10:12.166 --> 10:14.566
Gob, I have seen you
get passed over...

10:14.668 --> 10:16.966
time and time again
by your family.

10:17.070 --> 10:19.334
You don't deserve that.
You're smarter than them.

10:19.439 --> 10:24.172
What about macaroni...
let me finish... salad?

10:24.278 --> 10:26.769
Gob, this is your time.

10:26.880 --> 10:29.781
With my help,
knowing what I know...

10:29.883 --> 10:34.013
- we could take over the Bluth Company together.
- Wow!

10:34.121 --> 10:36.555
This is a side of you
I'd never noticed before.

10:36.657 --> 10:40.184
Have they always
been that big?

10:40.294 --> 10:42.387
<i>[Narrator] And the next day,</i>
<i>Michael went to his mother's.</i>

10:42.496 --> 10:45.522
I saw an exposé
on the Iraq palaces last night...

10:45.632 --> 10:48.192
and I could have sworn that one of them
was the Sea Wind unit.

10:48.302 --> 10:52.864
That's funny. I always pictured Iraq
in the middle of the desert.

10:52.973 --> 10:54.634
Dad sold houses to the Iraqis,
didn't he?

10:54.741 --> 10:57.266
And this is what you kept from me
so I could take the polygraph test.

10:57.377 --> 11:00.540
Tell me the truth, okay? 'Cause there's been
a lot of lying in this family.

11:00.647 --> 11:02.638
And a lot of love.

11:02.749 --> 11:05.274
- More lies.
- Look, I never knew about anything.

11:05.385 --> 11:07.683
But I had my suspicions.

11:07.788 --> 11:09.688
He never told me
where he was going...

11:09.790 --> 11:13.385
but he used to come back from those
business trips reeking of lamb.

11:13.493 --> 11:16.360
<i>And people would send figs</i>...
<i>not even at Christmas.</i>

11:16.463 --> 11:18.829
In the middle of October.

11:18.932 --> 11:21.162
Oh, and once,
someone sent him a toe...

11:21.268 --> 11:23.361
and he went white
as a sheet.

11:23.470 --> 11:26.564
- I think you're right, Michael.
- <i>[Door Opens]</i>

11:26.673 --> 11:30.074
<i>Zero hour, Michael.</i>
<i>It's the end of the line.</i>

11:30.177 --> 11:33.806
I'm the first born.
Sick of playing second fiddle.

11:33.914 --> 11:37.179
Always third in line for everything.
Tired of finishing fourth.

11:37.284 --> 11:39.752
Being the fifth wheel.

11:39.853 --> 11:42.287
There are six things
I'm mad about...

11:42.389 --> 11:45.256
- and I'm taking over.
- You want to be in charge?

11:45.359 --> 11:47.520
- Yeah.
- You want to deal with what I deal with...

11:47.628 --> 11:50.995
a sister who takes your money
and throws it away;

11:51.098 --> 11:52.998
a mother
who you can't trust;

11:53.100 --> 11:56.228
a company whose founder
may be on trial for treason...

11:56.336 --> 11:58.600
Is that what you want?

11:58.705 --> 12:03.142
- What kind of vacation time does it offer?
- Yeah.

12:03.243 --> 12:07.612
<i>[Narrator] Gob realized that the power play</i>
<i>he promised to make with Kitty...</i>

12:07.714 --> 12:10.774
- <i>had perhaps come at a bad time.</i>
- I've made a huge mistake.

12:10.884 --> 12:12.319
<i>And Tobias was having</i>
<i>his first book reading.</i>

12:12.319 --> 12:13.217
<i>And Tobias was having</i>
<i>his first book reading.</i>

12:13.320 --> 12:16.847
And, for the ease of the reader, I have
changed all the gender-related pronouns...

12:16.957 --> 12:19.858
"he," "she"...
to the masculine "he."

12:19.960 --> 12:24.260
<i>"The Man Inside Me.</i>
For Lindsay, my rock.

12:24.364 --> 12:26.855
I could not have done this
without him."

12:28.402 --> 12:31.132
<i>[Narrator] And Lindsay arrived</i>
<i>to support her husband.</i>

12:31.238 --> 12:35.698
"For there is a man inside me,
and only when he's finally out...

12:35.809 --> 12:39.210
can I walk free of pain."

12:39.313 --> 12:41.747
This book is gonna sell,
like, a billion copies.

12:41.848 --> 12:44.976
<i>Lindsay.!</i>
<i>Oh, I'm so glad you came.</i>

12:45.085 --> 12:47.019
I was hoping for more women.

12:47.120 --> 12:49.486
Perhaps I shouldn't have just used "he."
I think that was a mistake.

12:49.589 --> 12:53.753
<i>And Lindsay realized that Tobias was just</i>
<i>as oblivious as she'd always thought.</i>

12:53.860 --> 12:56.385
Tobias, I don't think
this relationship is gonna work.

12:56.496 --> 12:59.522
What are you talking about?
We've had some great times.

13:01.735 --> 13:04.670
We've got nothing left,
Tobias.

13:04.771 --> 13:07.137
<i>And Michael went</i>
<i>to confront his father.</i>

13:07.240 --> 13:10.835
You're building houses in Iraq? I mean,
do you know how they punish treason?

13:10.944 --> 13:13.174
- First time.
- I've never heard of a second.

13:13.280 --> 13:15.874
Oh, I've got the worst...
{ Beeps] attorneys.

13:15.982 --> 13:19.008
This is why I didn't want to get you
involved, but we can fix this.

13:19.119 --> 13:21.212
- What are Kitty's demands? What does she want?
- She wants my job.

13:21.321 --> 13:23.289
Suddenly everybody wants my job,
and I should've given it to her.

13:23.390 --> 13:27.690
You mean, you didn't? Michael! She has
the evidence of what we did over there.

13:27.794 --> 13:30.285
No, all she thinks it is
is unpaid taxes.

13:30.397 --> 13:33.230
Yeah. What if she gives it to someone
who's even moderately intelligent?

13:33.333 --> 13:36.393
<i>[Narrator] In fact, Kitty had gone</i>
<i>to someone moderately intelligent...</i>

13:36.503 --> 13:39.563
<i>in her continuing quest for</i>
<i>control of the Bluth Company.</i>

13:39.673 --> 13:43.404
- I can't believe you called me for a date.
- You didn't tell anyone, did you?

13:43.510 --> 13:46.445
Are you kidding?
I don't need to brag...

13:46.546 --> 13:49.140
<i>that some people haven't</i>
<i>even been on a date.!</i>

13:49.249 --> 13:51.649
Day not over yet, fatty.

13:51.752 --> 13:54.118
<i>You weren't thinking clearly.</i>
<i>I mean, none of us are.</i>

13:54.221 --> 13:56.121
We need bread.

13:56.223 --> 13:58.714
If this information was so damaging,
why didn't you just shred it?

13:58.825 --> 14:01.225
Well, Saddam
owed us money.

14:01.328 --> 14:04.126
You didn't realize
that he wouldn't pay?

14:04.231 --> 14:06.256
Your mom had a good
feeling about him.

14:06.366 --> 14:11.770
<i>So Mom knew this entire time, and shejust</i>
<i>lied to my face for months and months?</i>

14:11.872 --> 14:15.603
Let me tell you something, Dad. This is...
This is your problem. Okay? Not mine.

14:15.709 --> 14:19.805
Well, maybe it wouldn't be my problem
if you did what I asked for once in your life...

14:19.913 --> 14:23.041
- and you gave Kitty what I asked you to!
- Once in my damn life?

14:23.150 --> 14:26.142
All I've ever done my entire life is do
exactly what you told me to, all right?

14:26.253 --> 14:30.246
I've done everything for this family, Pop.
Not anymore. Kitty can have my job.

14:30.357 --> 14:32.917
And you can take your own
polygraph test, 'cause I'm done.

14:33.026 --> 14:36.120
- I'm done with you,
and I'm done with the business.
- <i>Great.</i>

14:36.229 --> 14:40.529
I'm gonna get a lethal injection
because my son won't eat a potato.

14:44.304 --> 14:46.966
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>George Sr., in a surprise move...</i>

14:47.073 --> 14:49.234
<i>volunteered to take</i>
<i>the polygraph.</i>

14:49.342 --> 14:51.367
- So did you swipe the sedative
from the infirmary...
- No!

14:51.478 --> 14:53.708
- to lower your heart rate?
- No! It's okay. I want to do this...

14:53.814 --> 14:57.147
because I want people to know
I never willfully deceived anyone.

14:57.250 --> 15:00.344
Mistakes were made,
but I never intended to hurt anyone!

15:00.454 --> 15:02.012
<i>I was trying to support</i>
<i>my family.!</i>

15:02.122 --> 15:04.352
- He doesn't appear to be on a sedative.
- But I can see clearly now...

15:04.458 --> 15:09.054
sitting in this chair, strapped to this machine,
I can see that my life has become a failure!

15:09.162 --> 15:12.495
<i>I've let people down,</i>
<i>let myself down.</i>

15:12.599 --> 15:16.228
But I love my country!
I love it here!

15:16.336 --> 15:18.998
You can shop... I love my...
Can't breathe.

15:19.105 --> 15:22.836
- I can't breathe!
- Wait! Wait! Are you guilty? Yes or no?

15:22.943 --> 15:25.605
- I think he's having a heart attack.
- <i>That was not a nod. No.</i>

15:25.712 --> 15:28.704
- That was not a nod.
- Call an ambulance!

15:28.815 --> 15:30.908
{ Siren Wailing]

15:32.285 --> 15:35.550
- Oh, how is he?
- Stable.

15:35.655 --> 15:38.852
But they don't know
if he's due for another one.

15:38.959 --> 15:43.089
It's his own fault. What kind of diet is this?
It's too much meat.

15:43.196 --> 15:46.290
I want all of you
off this immediately.

15:46.399 --> 15:49.129
Except you.

15:49.236 --> 15:51.898
<i>Tobias.!</i>
<i>I can't believe you came.!</i>

15:52.005 --> 15:55.031
Oh, come on, Lindsay.
This is my family.

15:55.141 --> 15:58.872
<i>[Narrator] And Lindsay realized that</i>
<i>perhaps they did have something left</i>...

15:58.979 --> 16:00.537
<i>a real connection.</i>

16:00.647 --> 16:03.207
Also, Dale, one of the gentlemen
from my reading...

16:03.316 --> 16:06.149
is a nurse here, so we were able
to park right out front.

16:08.021 --> 16:09.921
Oh! Barry.
Did you talk to a doctor?

16:10.023 --> 16:12.719
I did.
I have poison oak.

16:12.826 --> 16:15.556
Do you believe it?
Where the hell did I get that?

16:15.662 --> 16:17.562
<i>[Dog Barks]</i>

16:17.664 --> 16:20.394
- She was talking about George.
- No, he's the same.

16:20.500 --> 16:24.402
Look, I guess we should decide who's
gonna speak for the family. I would...

16:24.504 --> 16:26.062
but I have Laker tickets.

16:26.172 --> 16:28.072
<i>[Dog Barks]</i>

16:28.174 --> 16:30.074
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Buster knew this was his chance...</i>

16:30.176 --> 16:32.110
<i>to put Kitty's coup d'état</i>
<i>in action.</i>

16:32.212 --> 16:34.510
<i>He wondered</i>
<i>ifhe was up for it.</i>

16:34.614 --> 16:37.082
Someone might have to sign
the "do not resuscitate" form.

16:37.183 --> 16:41.244
- <i>And he decided he wasn't.</i>
- I need to make a telephone call.
Get out of something.

16:41.354 --> 16:43.447
I'm in charge now.

16:43.557 --> 16:45.752
I speak for this family.

16:45.859 --> 16:49.454
<i>I mean, l-I could,</i>
<i>if you wanted me to.</i>

16:49.563 --> 16:53.260
I'd rather not, obviously.
Don't know what I'd say.

16:53.366 --> 16:55.926
Why do I have to be the one?
I don't need this.

16:56.036 --> 16:58.300
<i>Why does this have to</i>
<i>become my problem? No. I'm out.</i>

16:58.405 --> 17:00.532
Forget it. Find somebody else.
I'm sick of it.

17:00.640 --> 17:04.269
- I'm sick of doing everything for this family.
- Where is Michael?

17:04.377 --> 17:06.607
- { Scoffs] Typical.
- Did somebody call him?

17:06.713 --> 17:08.704
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>In fact, they hadn't.</i>

17:08.815 --> 17:11.443
<i>And at that moment,</i>
<i>he was determined to finally get...</i>

17:11.550 --> 17:13.781
- <i>as far away from his family as possible.</i>
- Hey, pal.

17:13.887 --> 17:16.117
- Pack your bags.
- Where are we goin'?

17:16.222 --> 17:19.316
Anywhere. Joshua Tree, space camp,
the Baseball Hall of Fame...

17:19.425 --> 17:22.953
Everything you and I have always wanted to do
but haven't been able to because of this family.

17:23.063 --> 17:25.792
- We're just gonna go?
- Yeah. And I don't know
if we're even gonna come back.

17:25.898 --> 17:28.459
- There's nothing keeping us here.
- Well, Dad...

17:28.568 --> 17:32.004
- I like it here.
- What the hell's going on with you lately?

17:32.105 --> 17:35.268
I wanted to watch <i>Hindsight,</i>
and you weren't there.

17:35.375 --> 17:38.310
I want to pack up and desert the family,
and you don't want to.

17:38.411 --> 17:41.346
- Is it this new girlfriend?
- No, it...

17:41.448 --> 17:45.077
It's because of the family.
I like the family.

17:45.185 --> 17:48.916
- I mean, if we leave, who's
gonna take care of these people?
- I don't know.

17:49.022 --> 17:53.322
The state or the police. Maybe the
Magicians' Alliance will pick up some slack.

17:53.426 --> 17:56.361
- <i>[Phone Ringing]</i>
- Hey. That's gonna be them, and
they're gonna want something.

17:56.463 --> 17:58.590
We're not answering that.

17:58.698 --> 18:01.667
<i>[Ringing Continues]</i>

18:05.639 --> 18:07.539
Hello?

18:08.775 --> 18:11.767
- Where's George Michael?
- Exactly. Where is he?

18:11.878 --> 18:15.177
Ever since he's been dating this
Annie McNo-face, he's been blowing me off.

18:15.281 --> 18:17.511
- Oh, hey. Where's Pop-Pop?
- Room 212.

18:17.617 --> 18:19.185
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>And that's when Maeby decided...</i>

18:19.185 --> 18:20.083
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>And that's when Maeby decided...</i>

18:20.186 --> 18:24.247
<i>that perhaps she could use her uncle</i>
<i>to make her cousin jealous.</i>

18:27.260 --> 18:29.524
Hey, Dad.
Wait up.

18:29.629 --> 18:32.291
That was a waste
of time.

18:34.234 --> 18:36.930
- { Groaning]
- How's he doin'?

18:37.037 --> 18:39.198
He's hanging in there.

18:39.305 --> 18:41.705
<i>He keeps trying to get this I. V.</i>
<i>out ofhis arm. I don't understand why.</i>

18:41.808 --> 18:43.708
<i>It's just glucose.</i>

18:43.810 --> 18:46.210
We're all trying
to stay away from sugar.

18:48.048 --> 18:51.745
- He's gonna be okay, right?
- Absolutely. Absolutely. You all right?

18:51.851 --> 18:54.183
I'll handle
this one, Michael.

18:54.287 --> 18:59.088
Don't you worry. It'll take a lot more
than a heart attack to kill that old bear.

18:59.192 --> 19:01.092
{ Laughing]
Old bear!

19:01.194 --> 19:03.094
He likes the honey!

19:05.365 --> 19:07.731
He never got a chance
to see my bee business take off.

19:07.834 --> 19:11.361
Hey, come on, now. Dad's gonna be
around another 30 years, Gob.

19:11.471 --> 19:13.962
Your business,
uh, might not.

19:15.508 --> 19:17.772
You're a good brother,
Michael.

19:17.877 --> 19:21.836
Heart attack never stop
old Big Bear.

19:21.948 --> 19:24.940
I didn't even know
we were calling him Big Bear.

19:25.051 --> 19:28.919
- We never had a chance to!
- Hey, hey. Come on, Gob.

19:29.022 --> 19:33.459
Everybody, I'm very sorry, okay?
I feel awful. I should have been here.

19:33.560 --> 19:36.825
I was the one that was supposed to take that
polygraph test, and then I just turned on him...

19:36.930 --> 19:38.921
<i>and then this happened,</i>
<i>but never again, okay?</i>

19:39.032 --> 19:42.433
I will never, ever leave this family,
no matter what.

19:43.903 --> 19:47.600
- You should've been here.
- I feel like I covered that.

19:47.707 --> 19:50.642
- Well, you didn't say it.
- I feel awful. I should have been here.

19:50.744 --> 19:53.372
Maybe you're right. Maybe I didn't
say it. I should have been here.

19:55.615 --> 19:58.880
- Excuse me, Mr. Bluth.
- Hmm?

20:00.220 --> 20:02.780
- We lost him.
- { All Gasping]

20:02.889 --> 20:06.347
He just, uh, got away from us.
I'm sorry.

20:07.627 --> 20:09.822
<i>Uh, can we go in there?</i>

20:09.929 --> 20:12.397
If you want.
Not a lot to see.

20:12.499 --> 20:15.491
Maybe not for you,
but for us.

