<i>[Narrator] And that's when the family</i>
<i>realized that George Sr. wasn't dead...</i>

20:35.021 --> 20:38.081
<i>but was fleeing the country</i>
<i>that he loved so very much.</i>

20:44.931 --> 20:47.866
Pack your bags.

20:47.967 --> 20:50.731
<i>On the next season</i>
<i>of</i> Arrested Development.

20:50.837 --> 20:53.465
<i>The family grapples with the news</i>
<i>they hadjust heard.</i>

20:53.573 --> 20:56.041
Why would a doctor say he's "gone"
when he means he's escaped?

20:56.142 --> 20:58.167
God, I've missed bread.
Mmm.

20:58.278 --> 21:01.441
<i>Wouldn't you say,</i>
<i>"He left out the window'...</i>

21:01.548 --> 21:03.516
or, "The room's empty."

21:03.616 --> 21:05.516
<i>Maeby's life gets</i>
<i>a little more complicated.</i>

21:05.618 --> 21:09.054
It's so obvious. He gave himself the shot
to make it look like a heart attack.

21:09.155 --> 21:11.487
- How could they not see that?
- Maybe we should kiss again...

21:11.591 --> 21:15.027
and teach them a lesson
about obvious.

21:15.128 --> 21:16.925
<i>And Kitty helps George Sr.</i>
<i>escape.</i>

